Add Binary Strings
ğŸ“Œ Problem Description
Given two binary strings s1 and s2 consisting only of characters '0' and '1', compute their binary sum and return the result as a binary string.
Important Notes
Input strings may contain leading zeros
The output string must not contain leading zeros
The strings can be very large (up to 10â¶ characters), so numeric conversion is not allowed

ğŸ§  Approach

The solution simulates manual binary addition using string traversal:

Start from the rightmost characters of both strings

Add corresponding bits along with a carry

Store the result bit (sum % 2)

Update the carry (sum // 2)

Continue until all bits and carry are processed

Remove leading zeros from the final result

This approach ensures efficiency even for very large inputs.

âš™ï¸ Algorithm

Initialize two pointers at the end of both strings

Use a variable to track carry

Iterate while either pointer is valid or carry exists

Append each computed bit to a result list

Reverse the result and strip leading zeros
